content:
From my understanding the royalties of 3.5% are split 2.5%/1%. The 2.5% belongs to the Motoko Ghost NFT community. You know, the members here who have been buying all the nft's and supporting this collection/brand for almost 3 years now. A Motoko DAO is being established for a variety of reasons but primarily to take custody of that asset and vote on its distribution.

The other 1% is a hardcoded marketplace fee, which Stephen (CTO Toniq) put in place to direct all mp fees to Toniq. Stephen created the EXT standard and the Motoko Ghost canister. He was posting here in February but then disappeared. 

@bobbodily has suggested that the DAO should now retrospectively allocate funds to Poked despite prior contracts stating these royalties belong to the Motoko Ghost community. Here is an alternative suggestion. Bob/Stephen/Toniq have been receiving a 1% mp fee since the beginning. If they want, take half of those mp's fees since 2021 and send them to Poked. Whatever the case, we will soon have a DAO to vote on all these matters.
